<br>As with anything, some people may experience an allergic reaction when using essential oils. If you’re applying essential oils to your skin, you should always mix them with a carrier oil first. This is because essential oils are extremely potent and can cause skin irritation if applied undiluted. It’s also important to do a patch test to check for skin irritation before using the oil more liberally. <br>
<br>Should you experience any symptoms of an allergic reaction, you should stop using the essential oil immediately, rinse any oil from your skin and contact your medical provider for advice. <br>
<br>If you are pregnant, breastfeeding or have a health condition, you should always consult your medical provider before using essential oils, as certain oils may not be compatible with certain health conditions. 
